text: Jonathan Walasiak (born 23 October 1982 in Mons) is a Belgian football player who has been in the national team. He last played for Royal Albert Quévy-Mons and is a right midfielder. ==Career== Walasiak played professional football in Belgium and Hungary, beginning his career at Standard. ==References== ==External links == * * Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:Belgian footballers Category:Belgian people of Polish descent Category:Belgium international footballers Category:Belgian expatriate footballers Category:Belgian First Division A players Category:Ligue 1 players Category:Standard Liège players Category:FC Metz players Category:R.E.
